msgctxt "an10.67:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.67:0.2"
msgid "7. Yamakavagga "
msgstr "7. Pairs "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.67:0.3"
msgid "67. Paṭhamanaḷakapānasutta "
msgstr "67. At Naḷakapāna (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an10.67:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena naḷakapānaṃ nāma kosalānaṃ nigamo tadavasari. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a town of the Kosalans named Naḷakapāna. "

# NOTE: BB follows PTS in calling this “Judas tree”, but this appears to be a mistake. The dict says palas=Butea frondosa=Judas tree, but the Judas tree is in fact Cercis siliquastrum, which anyway is probably not native to India. The Butea Frondosa or Monosperma is called “Flame of the Forest”, parrot tree or bastard teak.
msgctxt "an10.67:1.2"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā naḷakapāne viharati palāsavane. "
msgstr "There the Buddha stayed near Naḷakapāna in the parrot tree grove. "

msgctxt "an10.67:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā tadahuposathe bhikkhusaṅghaparivuto nisinno hoti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time it was the sabbath, and the Buddha was sitting surrounded by the Saṅgha of monks. "

msgctxt "an10.67:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bahudeva rattiṃ bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā tuṇhībhūtaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ anuviloketvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "The Buddha spent most of the night educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the mendicants with a Dhamma talk. Then he looked around the Saṅgha of monks, who were so very silent. He addressed Venerable Sāriputta: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.123, sc2
#. VAR: Vigatathinamiddho → vigatathīnamiddho (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an10.67:2.1"
msgid "“Vigatathinamiddho kho, sāriputta, bhikkhusaṃgho. "
msgstr "“Sāriputta, the Saṅgha of mendicants is rid of dullness and drowsiness. "

msgctxt "an10.67:2.2"
msgid "Paṭibhātu taṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhūnaṃ dhammī kathā. "
msgstr "Give them some Dhamma talk as you feel inspired. "

msgctxt "an10.67:2.3"
msgid "Piṭṭhi me āgilāyati; "
msgstr "My back is sore, "

msgctxt "an10.67:2.4"
msgid "tamahaṃ āyamissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "I’ll stretch it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.67:2.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Sāriputta replied. "

# NOTE: catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññāpetvā means “having spread out a four-fold sanghati”. BB translates thus in MN, but in SN and AN evidently takes pannapeti to refer to the act of folding rather than spreading. this is unlikely, since pannapeti is the standard term for setting out a seat. If we apply this to folding the robe, then the passages do not actually have the bit about making a seat. Furthermore, in SN he inconsistently takes pannapeti in a causal sense “had his robe folded”, but there are plenty of places that show this cannot work, as for example SN 16.11, where Kassapa obviously spreads out his own folded robe: the only other person present was the Buddha!
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an10.67:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññāpetvā dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappesi pāde pādaṃ accādhāya sato sampajāno uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā. "
msgstr "And then the Buddha spread out his outer robe folded in four and laid down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up. "

msgctxt "an10.67:3.2"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "an10.67:3.3"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.67:3.4"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied. "

msgctxt "an10.67:3.5"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca: "
msgstr "Sāriputta said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: hirī → hiri (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an10.67:4.1"
msgid "“Yassa kassaci, āvuso, saddhā natthi kusalesu dhammesu, hirī natthi … "
msgstr "“Reverends, whoever has no faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom when it comes to skillful qualities "

msgctxt "an10.67:4.2"
msgid "ottappaṃ natthi … "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: vīriyaṃ → viriyaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an10.67:4.3"
msgid "vīriyaṃ natthi … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.67:4.4"
msgid "paññā natthi kusalesu dhammesu, tassa yā ratti vā divaso vā āgacchati, hāniyeva pāṭikaṅkhā kusalesu dhammesu no vuddhi. "
msgstr "can expect decline, not growth, in skillful qualities, whether by day or by night. "

msgctxt "an10.67:4.5"
